# Shell Commands with TaskGo! (CRITICAL)

## The Root Cause

The app is named "TaskGo!" -- the `!` character triggers **zsh history expansion** inside double quotes, causing the shell to hang indefinitely.

`killall "TaskGo!"` -- HANGS (! triggers history expansion)
`killall 'TaskGo!'` -- WORKS (single quotes prevent interpretation)

This applies to EVERY shell command that references the app name or path containing `!`.

## Rules (MUST FOLLOW)

1. **ALWAYS use single quotes** around any string containing `TaskGo!` or any path with `!`
2. **NEVER use double quotes** around strings containing `!`
3. **NEVER chain kill commands with &&** to the build. Use `;` so build runs regardless.

## Correct Commands

Kill the app:
```bash
killall 'TaskGo!' 2>/dev/null || true
```

Build:
```bash
xcodebuild -project TaskGo/TaskGo.xcodeproj -scheme TaskGo -configuration Debug build 2>&1 | tail -5
```

Launch:
```bash
open '/Users/crucegauntlet/Library/Developer/Xcode/DerivedData/TaskGo-gbsqnqzrmpfrzpaghxowvfsqppoi/Build/Products/Debug/TaskGo!.app'
```

Full deploy sequence (each step separate, using ; not &&):
```bash
killall 'TaskGo!' 2>/dev/null || true; sleep 1
```
Then build separately. Then open separately.

## NEVER DO THIS

```bash
killall "TaskGo!"          # HANGS - ! in double quotes
open "...TaskGo!.app"      # HANGS - ! in double quotes  
pkill -f "TaskGo!"         # HANGS - matches itself AND ! issue
```
